x = 1
y = 1

    if divisors[i] == 1:
        continue
    if i < N - 1 and divisors[i] == divisors[i + 1]:
        x *= divisors[i]
        i += 1

        y *= divisors[i]

def get_divisors(n):
    divisors = []
    for i in range(1, int(n**0.5) + 1):
        if n % i == 0:
            divisors.append(i)
            if i != n // i:
                divisors.append(n // i)

    return divisors


def main():
    N = int(input())
    divisors = list(map(int, input().split()))

            continue
        if divisors[i] == divisors[i + 1]:
            x *= divisors[i]
            i += 1
        else:
            y *= divisors[i]
    print(x, y)
